A metal beam is fixed into a wall and experiences two pairs of couple forces. If [`\overrightarrow{F_1}`] has a magnitude of [`[$F_C] \: \textrm{lbs}`] and the beam experiences a total moment of [`[$M_T] \: \textrm{lb} \cdot \textrm{ft}`] counterclockwise, find the magnitude of [`\overrightarrow{F}`]. Assume that the length of the beam is [`[$L] \: \textrm{ft}`] and that the beam has negligible mass. Let [`d_1 = [$d_1] \: \textrm{ft}`].


Find the magnitude of [`\overrightarrow{F_2}`].

[`||\overrightarrow{F_2}|| =`] [___]{"$F_C"} [`\: \textrm{lbs}`]


Find the magnitude of [`\overrightarrow{F}`].

[`||\overrightarrow{F}|| =`] [___]{"$F"} [`\: \textrm{lbs}`]


END_PGML

